A survey conducted by the UK Employment and Training Commission in 2014 showed that 17% of the reasons why employers struggle to fill vacancies can be attributed to a lack of language skills.
Therefore, knowledge of languages is becoming increasingly necessary in preparing young people for their future career path.
In future job opportunities that require language proficiency, these skills are essential in a global world.
If someone learns another language, regardless of the career path he chooses, with such lifelong knowledge, he has a great advantage in the future.
A multilingual person who can communicate directly with people from foreign countries automatically has an advantage over the competition.
A 2013 YouGov survey of more than 4,000 adults in the UK showed that 75 percent of people did not speak a foreign language well enough to be able to speak, with French being the only language spoken by a double-digit percentage of respondents, which is 15 percent.
Therefore, investing in language learning is important for today’s children.
With the knowledge of several languages, especially those from developing countries, children have a better chance of finding a suitable job.
In Scotland, schools differ in the languages they teach.
Many schools focus on more classical modern languages, while others teach languages that are expected to be the most important for the UK in 2020, such as Mandarin or Japanese.
Regardless of the interests of your child, it will always be possible to choose a number of languages taught by experts in this field in independent schools.
Scottish Independent Schools are committed to providing a learning environment that will prepare and equip children with the knowledge they need to succeed, no matter what the future brings.
In the global business environment, it cannot be denied that languages remain extremely important for the future of the country, so this must also be expressed in education.
In fact, modern languages should be regarded as “international communication skills.”
Independent schools will continue to offer this choice, diversity and excellence to young people in Scotland.
You have to do it right.
